1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:02,640
It's finally become a quiet, nice night.

3
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:05,080
Huh? Why am I outside?

4
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:08,070
Oh, well. I'm sleepy. I'm gonna sleep.

5
00:02:10,150 --> 00:02:16,160
I never thought that four agents
with numbers under twelve would lose!

6
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:19,490
But where are you
planning to escape to?!

7
00:02:19,490 --> 00:02:23,430
In any case, we'll hide somewhere
until they leave this island and...

8
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:27,360
Ahh! The Unluckies!

9
00:02:29,770 --> 00:02:31,940
H-Hold on a sec!

10
00:02:31,940 --> 00:02:34,170
We're not running away! It's not that...

11
00:02:34,170 --> 00:02:37,700
Please! Don't report to the boss!

12
00:02:43,450 --> 00:02:44,610
Hold it!

13
00:02:46,790 --> 00:02:51,120
This town is quite lively
despite how late it is.

14
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:55,460
Ha! What a boring job he gave us...

15
00:02:55,460 --> 00:02:59,130
sending us all the way
to the front lines...

16
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:12,640
Hm?

17
00:03:16,650 --> 00:03:22,490
I can't fall in a place like this.
I've got an important mission...

18
00:03:22,490 --> 00:03:24,490
How pitiful...

19
00:03:24,490 --> 00:03:27,160
losing against just one swordsman...

20
00:03:27,160 --> 00:03:28,830
Hm?!

21
00:03:28,830 --> 00:03:32,500
Mr. 5! Miss Valentine!

22
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:35,830
Are you guys kidding around? Huh?

23
00:03:37,340 --> 00:03:41,170
After all, this is the difference
between our rank and yours, isn't it?

24
00:03:41,170 --> 00:03:43,680
Did you come to laugh at us?

25
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:45,840
That, too, but...

26
00:03:47,850 --> 00:03:50,010
Of course, we're here
under our mission.

27
00:03:51,180 --> 00:03:55,520
Thank goodness. If you help us,
that man is no match for us!

28
00:03:55,520 --> 00:04:00,530
That's right. Please beat
that swordsman right away.

29
00:04:00,530 --> 00:04:04,530
Huh? Enough with the bad jokes.

30
00:04:04,530 --> 00:04:07,200
Us help you?

31
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:10,540
Did you really think that
we'd come all the way

32
00:04:10,540 --> 00:04:13,200
to the end of the Grand Line for that?

33
00:04:14,540 --> 00:04:17,440
What? Then what mission
did you come here for?

34
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:19,550
You really have no idea?

35
00:04:19,550 --> 00:04:24,970
There're big criminals here that
the boss sent us here to deal with.

36
00:04:26,180 --> 00:04:26,650
Huh?!

37
00:04:26,650 --> 00:04:31,160
These're the boss' words:
"They've found out my secrets."

38
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:34,160
Of course, I don't even know what
kind of secrets they are, but...

39
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:36,500
our company's motto is "Mystery."

40
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:41,170
No matter whose identity it is,
the rule is that you never nose around.

41
00:04:41,170 --> 00:04:44,770
If someone finds out the boss' secrets,

42
00:04:44,770 --> 00:04:48,540
that's, of course,
a sin worthy of death.

43
00:04:48,540 --> 00:04:54,500
So, when we carefully investigated who
had learned his secrets we found out...

44
00:04:55,850 --> 00:04:57,010
Oh boy...

45
00:04:57,480 --> 00:05:03,520
That agents from a certain kingdom
have infiltrated Baroque Works.

46
00:05:03,520 --> 00:05:06,860
A certain kingdom? W-Wait a sec!

47
00:05:06,860 --> 00:05:10,030
Although I'm wearing a crown,
I'm not a king or anything!

48
00:05:10,030 --> 00:05:11,860
It's just my hobby!

49
00:05:11,860 --> 00:05:13,200
We're not talking about you!

50
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:18,540
The sinners are those who're missing
from Alabasta Kingdom right now...

51
00:05:18,540 --> 00:05:22,030
They know! It's all over!

52
00:05:23,010 --> 00:05:23,570
Die!

53
00:05:23,570 --> 00:05:25,010
Igarappappa!

54
00:05:26,010 --> 00:05:28,720
I won't let you lay
a finger on our princess!

55
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:31,960
On my name as squad captain
of Alabasta Kingdom Security!

56
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:33,320
Igaram!

57
00:05:35,030 --> 00:05:38,130
Igaram, squad captain
of Alabasta Kingdom Security!

58
00:05:38,130 --> 00:05:40,460
And Princess Nefertari Vivi!

59
00:05:40,460 --> 00:05:45,420
In the name of the Baroque Works'
boss, we'll eliminate you two.

60
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:57,470
The Secret Criminal Organization

61
00:05:58,050 --> 00:05:59,850
Damn...

62
00:05:59,850 --> 00:06:03,280
And I left Luffy down there, too.

63
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:05,920
Quickly, Princess Vivi! Please escape!

64
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:07,180
Igaram!

65
00:06:21,570 --> 00:06:22,500
Igaram!

66
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:23,330
It's no use!

67
00:06:36,950 --> 00:06:38,990
You monsters!

68
00:06:38,990 --> 00:06:42,720
You're a princess, Miss Wednesday?!

69
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:45,630
Quit being dumb, Mr. 9!

70
00:06:45,630 --> 00:06:48,490
This is one screwed-up night!
You guys can do whatever you want!

71
00:06:53,260 --> 00:06:56,590
You think you can escape from us?

72
00:06:57,660 --> 00:06:59,250
Don't mess with me!

73
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:05,530
I'm having a hard time
swallowing what's going on here,

74
00:07:05,530 --> 00:07:07,270
but we've been a pair for a long time.

75
00:07:07,270 --> 00:07:09,100
I'll buy you some time!

76
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:12,010
Get going, Miss Wednesday!

77
00:07:12,010 --> 00:07:13,910
Mr. 9!

78
00:07:13,910 --> 00:07:15,910
Pretty manly, wouldn't you say?

79
00:07:15,910 --> 00:07:17,850
Bye bye, baby!

80
00:07:17,850 --> 00:07:21,330
Hot-blooded Bat...

81
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:19,870
Mr. 9!

82
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:27,490
All we need is the will to
accomplish our missions.

83
00:07:27,490 --> 00:07:30,490
A pathetic sense of camaraderie
will only bring about death.

84
00:07:30,490 --> 00:07:31,840
Time to learn that the hard way!

85
00:07:31,840 --> 00:07:33,370
Nose Fancy...

86
00:07:33,370 --> 00:07:35,470
...of Guts!

87
00:07:35,470 --> 00:07:36,340
...Cannon!

88
00:07:41,740 --> 00:07:43,570
Mr. 9!

89
00:07:43,570 --> 00:07:46,370
Whoa, now! That's some
dangerous snot he's got!

90
00:07:48,410 --> 00:07:49,980
What the hell?!

91
00:07:49,980 --> 00:07:51,080
Sir Swordsman!

92
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:54,550
Upon seeing your skill, I have
a request, unreasonable as it may be!

93
00:07:54,550 --> 00:07:58,020
Yeah, right! Screw that! Let go of me!

94
00:07:58,020 --> 00:08:03,260
As both of those people possess
devil fruit powers, I can't stop them!

95
00:08:03,260 --> 00:08:07,030
Might I ask you to protect
the princess in my place?!

96
00:08:07,030 --> 00:08:08,300
Please!

97
00:08:08,830 --> 00:08:10,320
Karoo! Run!

98
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:12,900
There she goes.

99
00:08:12,900 --> 00:08:16,100
She can't get away from us.
Let's get her, Miss Valentine!

100
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:18,240
Right, Mr. 5!

101
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:24,340
If you can safely deliver the princess to the
great kingdom of Alabasta far east of here...

102
00:08:24,340 --> 00:08:27,780
I promise that you will
be rewarded immensely!

103
00:08:27,780 --> 00:08:29,290
I humbly beg of you!

104
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:32,350
Please, keep the princess safe!

105
00:08:32,350 --> 00:08:36,820
Screw that! You were trying to
kill us until just a minute ago!

106
00:08:36,820 --> 00:08:38,420
Don't make me cut you some more!

107
00:08:38,420 --> 00:08:41,590
Is this "immense reward" for real?

108
00:08:41,590 --> 00:08:44,980
I'll take up that offer!
How does one billion belly sound?

109
00:08:44,980 --> 00:08:46,260
Nami!

110
00:08:46,260 --> 00:08:49,000
O-One billion bel–

111
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,500
♪ Ma, ma, ma... ♪

112
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:52,840
I thought you were asleep.

113
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:55,210
Come on, now.

114
00:08:55,210 --> 00:08:58,140
Who in their right mind
would sleep carelessly

115
00:08:58,140 --> 00:09:00,040
in an overly-suspicious town
that welcomes pirates?

116
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:02,580
It was all an act! A-C-T, act!

117
00:09:02,580 --> 00:09:05,420
I could keep on going if I wanted!

118
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:06,520
That so?

119
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:09,190
♪ Ma, ma, ma... ♪

120
00:09:09,190 --> 00:09:13,690
So, will you promise us
the one billion, Squad Captain?

121
00:09:13,690 --> 00:09:18,060
If you don't ask for our help,
your princess probably will die...

122
00:09:19,460 --> 00:09:24,230
A mere soldier like me can't
promise such large sums of money...

123
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:28,910
You're not suggesting a princess
is worth less than that, are you?

124
00:09:28,910 --> 00:09:31,110
Pay up.

125
00:09:31,110 --> 00:09:33,880
Now she's threatening him!

126
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:37,350
In that case, if you're willing to
safely deliver the princess there,

127
00:09:37,350 --> 00:09:41,820
it would be best if you negotiate
the terms with her directly!

128
00:09:41,820 --> 00:09:43,920
Meaning I gotta start
by saving her, huh?

129
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:47,290
Even as we speak, her life is in danger!

130
00:09:47,290 --> 00:09:50,990
Alright, then. I'll save
your princess for now.

131
00:09:52,930 --> 00:09:54,700
Okay! Go get her, Zoro!

132
00:09:54,700 --> 00:09:56,500
Yeah, right, you idiot!

133
00:09:56,500 --> 00:10:00,500
Why do I have to go along
with your money-making schemes?!

134
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:02,590
Man, you're dense!

135
00:10:02,590 --> 00:10:08,550
My money is mine, but my
contracts belong to all of you!

136
00:10:08,550 --> 00:10:11,180
That's the kind of logic
a bully would use!

137
00:10:11,180 --> 00:10:14,220
What's the big deal?! All you
gotta do is cut those guys down!

138
00:10:14,220 --> 00:10:18,060
I don't like being used,
unlike that idiot cook!

139
00:10:18,060 --> 00:10:21,460
You're just afraid you can't beat them!

140
00:10:21,460 --> 00:10:24,030
What?! Just try saying
that some more!

141
00:10:24,030 --> 00:10:27,100
You're just afraid you can't beat them!

142
00:10:25,310 --> 00:10:27,100
Bathroom.

143
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:29,000
Quit repeating that crap!

144
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:33,220
Hey, now. Have you forgotten?
You owe me money.

145
00:10:33,220 --> 00:10:35,650
Huh? I don't owe you a thing.

146
00:10:36,070 --> 00:10:40,280
I lent you 100,000 belly
for some swords in Loguetown.

147
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:43,510
I gave you the 100,000 right back!

148
00:10:43,510 --> 00:10:46,650
Someone gave me some swords,
so I didn't use the money!

149
00:10:46,650 --> 00:10:52,610
But you did agree to pay me back
300 percent—300,000 Belly total.

150
00:10:55,030 --> 00:10:56,760
There's something I wanna buy.

151
00:10:56,760 --> 00:11:00,100
You'll owe me 300 percent
of what I lend you!

152
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:03,400
You haven't paid back
the other 200,000 belly yet.

153
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:07,910
I gave you the 100,000 belly
back the same day! Gimme a break!

154
00:11:07,910 --> 00:11:10,210
Nope!

155
00:11:10,210 --> 00:11:13,510
Can't you keep even a single promise?

156
00:11:15,650 --> 00:11:18,550
Do what I say,
and maybe I'll call us even!

157
00:11:18,550 --> 00:11:21,620
D-Dammit! You're not gonna
die a good death, you know!

158
00:11:21,620 --> 00:11:24,620
Yeah. I'm going to hell.

159
00:11:24,620 --> 00:11:26,100
Damn woman!

160
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:27,870
Thanks a bunch!

161
00:11:28,690 --> 00:11:31,230
I'm so ashamed...

162
00:11:31,230 --> 00:11:35,900
If only I'd been stronger,
I could have protected the princess!

163
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:39,320
Don't worry about it!
He's insanely strong!

164
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:43,470
If anything should happen to
her highness—to Princess Vivi...

165
00:11:43,470 --> 00:11:48,010
the kingdom of Alabasta
would be finished...

166
00:11:48,010 --> 00:11:50,980
She must live!

167
00:11:51,980 --> 00:11:52,910
Run!

168
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:57,370
Run, Karoo!

169
00:11:59,160 --> 00:12:01,890
There's a ship docked
behind the cactus rocks!

170
00:12:04,170 --> 00:12:05,500
Karoo! Stop!

171
00:12:09,350 --> 00:12:10,480
They've found us!

172
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:12,050
Karoo! This way! Hurry!

173
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:17,020
Such pointless struggling.

174
00:12:20,130 --> 00:12:21,530
Miss Monday!

175
00:12:22,530 --> 00:12:26,000
Go on. You can get to
the ships through here.

176
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,860
I'll hold them off here!

177
00:12:27,860 --> 00:12:29,800
But...

178
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:31,970
Thanks to that
freakishly-strong swordsman,

179
00:12:31,970 --> 00:12:35,100
we're all going to get punished
for failing our mission anyway.

180
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:41,070
Plus I'd much rather get my
butt kicked shielding a friend.

181
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:43,440
Get going!

182
00:12:46,650 --> 00:12:47,850
Thank you.

183
00:12:49,860 --> 00:12:53,450
First Mr. 9, and now you...

184
00:12:53,700 --> 00:12:55,290
Miss Monday?

185
00:12:55,460 --> 00:12:57,390
I won't let you pass.

186
00:12:58,840 --> 00:12:59,860
You're so funny!

187
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:04,210
You're a disgrace...

188
00:13:10,580 --> 00:13:12,910
to Baroque Works!

189
00:13:24,280 --> 00:13:25,960
Miss Monday...

190
00:13:27,780 --> 00:13:32,130
I'm a bomb man—I can
make my entire body explode.

191
00:13:32,130 --> 00:13:36,470
Thanks to this Bomb-Bomb Fruit power,
there is no mission I've never completed!

192
00:13:38,660 --> 00:13:41,630
There is no possible escape from us.

193
00:13:43,190 --> 00:13:44,940
Take this!

194
00:13:44,940 --> 00:13:46,760
Nose Fancy...

195
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:48,430
Cannon!

196
00:13:54,410 --> 00:13:55,910
Mr. Bushido!

197
00:13:59,380 --> 00:14:02,120
Th-The street...!

198
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:03,820
Who's he?

199
00:14:05,730 --> 00:14:07,800
I cut his booger!

200
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:09,830
Damn you! You never give up!

201
00:14:09,830 --> 00:14:11,060
Now, of all times!

202
00:14:14,300 --> 00:14:16,670
Don't get hasty.
I'm here to rescue you.

203
00:14:16,670 --> 00:14:18,900
Huh? Me?

204
00:14:25,010 --> 00:14:27,670
Much better! Now for more sleep!

205
00:14:29,110 --> 00:14:30,750
What in the world?!

206
00:14:36,060 --> 00:14:37,290
Say...

207
00:14:37,620 --> 00:14:41,260
What is Baroque Works, anyway?

208
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:45,230
A secret criminal organization.

209
00:14:45,420 --> 00:14:49,830
None of its members knows
their boss' face or name.

210
00:14:49,830 --> 00:14:54,700
Its main work is espionage, assassination,
larceny, and bounty-hunting.

211
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:58,110
It's all done at their boss' command.

212
00:14:59,100 --> 00:15:03,680
Why would they listen to their boss,
whose identity they don't know?

213
00:15:04,290 --> 00:15:10,230
Baroque Works' ultimate objective
is the founding of an ideal nation!

214
00:15:10,230 --> 00:15:13,470
Everyone who does well
within the company now

215
00:15:13,470 --> 00:15:16,800
will be guaranteed a high social
standing within the ideal nation

216
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:20,340
that the boss will be
creating before long.

217
00:15:20,340 --> 00:15:22,780
I see...

218
00:15:22,780 --> 00:15:26,280
The boss' codename is Mr. 0.

219
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:31,280
In other words, the closer
a person's codename is to zero,

220
00:15:31,280 --> 00:15:34,220
the higher that person's
future standing will be...

221
00:15:34,220 --> 00:15:36,590
and more than anything,
the stronger they are!

222
00:15:36,590 --> 00:15:43,610
The strength of those from Mr. 5
and above is especially incredible.

223
00:15:45,090 --> 00:15:50,770
So you're the swordsman who cut down
all of the lowly employees in this town.

224
00:15:50,770 --> 00:15:53,740
Why would you want to protect
the princess of Alabasta?

225
00:15:53,740 --> 00:15:56,710
I got some circumstances
of my own, you see...

226
00:15:56,710 --> 00:16:00,880
Well, no matter. You're our enemy,
one way or the other.

227
00:16:00,880 --> 00:16:03,050
You're in our way.

228
00:16:03,050 --> 00:16:05,310
Yeah! He is!

229
00:16:05,310 --> 00:16:10,480
There you are!

230
00:16:11,710 --> 00:16:14,320
Zoro!

231
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:16,390
Now what?!

232
00:16:16,390 --> 00:16:17,630
Luffy!

233
00:16:17,630 --> 00:16:19,390
Thanks, but I don't need any help!

234
00:16:19,390 --> 00:16:22,550
Or does that wench
got you in debt, too?

235
00:16:23,820 --> 00:16:27,690
I'm gonna make you pay
for what you did! Let's fight!

236
00:16:27,690 --> 00:16:29,160
Huh?!

237
00:16:29,160 --> 00:16:31,960
What nonsense are you
spewing this time?!

238
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:33,000
Shut up!

239
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:36,970
I'm gonna kick your ass
for being such an ingrate!

240
00:16:36,970 --> 00:16:38,410
Ingrate?!

241
00:16:38,580 --> 00:16:40,110
That's right!

242
00:16:41,420 --> 00:16:43,820
Hey! What happened?!
Who did this to you?!

243
00:16:43,820 --> 00:16:47,860
Your green-haired swordsman friend...

244
00:16:47,860 --> 00:16:49,490
What?!

245
00:16:50,490 --> 00:16:55,200
Everyone in town welcomed us
and gave us lots of yummy food!

246
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:58,540
But you cut down
every last one of them!

247
00:16:58,540 --> 00:17:01,840
Well, yeah, but...

248
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:03,800
You will pay for this!

249
00:17:04,240 --> 00:17:06,070
What a dull-headed person!

250
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:10,610
Internal strife, huh? Talk about lame.

251
00:17:10,610 --> 00:17:14,900
Let's just get rid of everyone
who interferes with our mission!

252
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:16,110
Hold on, Luffy.

253
00:17:16,110 --> 00:17:18,980
Listen to me. They were
actually bounty hunt–

254
00:17:18,980 --> 00:17:21,020
Don't make excuses!

255
00:17:21,020 --> 00:17:22,110
What?!

256
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:26,790
Are you trying to kill me?!

257
00:17:26,790 --> 00:17:28,340
Yeah! Die!

258
00:17:29,290 --> 00:17:31,550
Dammit! Listen to me!

259
00:17:33,030 --> 00:17:34,020
Hey!

260
00:17:37,030 --> 00:17:38,760
That idiot!

261
00:17:38,760 --> 00:17:39,990
He's serious!

262
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:43,270
Mr. 5.

263
00:17:43,270 --> 00:17:46,670
It doesn't seem like
they're here to stop us.

264
00:17:46,670 --> 00:17:48,070
It would seem not.

265
00:17:48,070 --> 00:17:52,340
Then let's accomplish
our mission quickly.

266
00:17:52,340 --> 00:17:55,610
Our mission to eliminate Princess
Vivi of the Kingdom of Alabasta.

267
00:17:55,610 --> 00:17:57,360
Why, you! Quit running away!

268
00:17:57,360 --> 00:17:58,920
H-Hold on, Luffy! Hear me out!

269
00:17:58,920 --> 00:18:00,620
Let's do it, Miss Valentine!

270
00:18:00,620 --> 00:18:01,890
Yes, Mr. 5!

271
00:18:03,060 --> 00:18:06,050
Quit screwing around, dammit!

272
00:18:12,660 --> 00:18:14,330
That dumbass!

273
00:18:21,970 --> 00:18:26,110
Now you guys've really
gotten in our way!

274
00:18:26,110 --> 00:18:28,580
Ugh! What the heck's going on?!

275
00:18:28,580 --> 00:18:31,850
If you two wanna kill
each other that badly,

276
00:18:31,850 --> 00:18:36,050
then we'll kill you both
ourselves while we're at it!

277
00:18:36,050 --> 00:18:37,250
'Kay?

278
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:44,230
Now I'm really annoyed!

279
00:18:44,230 --> 00:18:47,470
Time to die at the hands of
my Kilo-Kilo Fruit power!

280
00:18:48,870 --> 00:18:49,980
Get ready!

281
00:18:49,980 --> 00:18:53,420
As I ride this explosive blast,
I weigh only one kilogram!

282
00:18:54,070 --> 00:18:56,440
Mr. Bushido! You have
to dodge! She's...!

283
00:18:56,440 --> 00:18:57,780
Shut up!

284
00:18:59,410 --> 00:19:01,590
This isn't the time for that right now!

285
00:19:05,090 --> 00:19:08,790
That was a good workout!
Finally managed to digest that food!

286
00:19:08,790 --> 00:19:11,890
M-Mr. 5?! No way!

287
00:19:11,890 --> 00:19:14,730
He took out a Baroque
Works officer agent?!

288
00:19:14,730 --> 00:19:17,200
Now I can fight for reals.

289
00:19:17,440 --> 00:19:20,940
Hold on, Luffy.
Calm down and hear me out.

290
00:19:17,670 --> 00:19:19,310
Here I come!

291
00:19:19,310 --> 00:19:25,420
I can change to 10,000 kilograms!

292
00:19:20,940 --> 00:19:23,550
Everyone in town was
a bounty hunter—

293
00:19:23,550 --> 00:19:25,420
our enemy, in other words.

294
00:19:26,210 --> 00:19:27,950
Hey! Don't ignore me!

295
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:32,620
Liar! Enemies wouldn't
give us food to eat!

296
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:34,090
Take this!

297
00:19:34,090 --> 00:19:36,110
10,000 Kilo Press!

298
00:19:37,780 --> 00:19:38,770
Luffy.

299
00:19:41,490 --> 00:19:44,460
Looks like trying to talk
sense into you is pointless.

300
00:19:47,220 --> 00:19:49,760
You dumb dimwit!

301
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:52,130
In that case, I'm gonna
fight to kill, too!

302
00:19:52,130 --> 00:19:54,030
Don't regret it when you die!

303
00:19:54,030 --> 00:19:55,730
Sounds great to me!

304
00:19:55,730 --> 00:19:58,470
Hold on! What's going on?!

305
00:19:58,470 --> 00:20:00,660
Weren't these two people friends?!

306
00:20:01,570 --> 00:20:05,130
Gum-Gum...

307
00:20:06,740 --> 00:20:07,560
Oni...

308
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:11,870
– ...Bazooka!
– ...Giri!

309
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:24,960
This is the perfect chance
to see which is stronger,

310
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:26,600
brute force or swordsmanship!

311
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:30,270
Yeah! Let's find out
once and for all!

312
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:33,240
Dragon Twister!

313
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:36,650
Gum-Gum...

314
00:20:36,650 --> 00:20:38,170
Pistol!

315
00:21:00,860 --> 00:21:01,800
What now?

316
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:06,130
I want to escape, but will we be
all right if we pass through here?

317
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:26,900
Damn it!

318
00:21:26,900 --> 00:21:29,540
The title of Baroque
Works Officer Agent

319
00:21:29,540 --> 00:21:32,940
will be shamed if we let
these guys make fools of us!

320
00:21:32,940 --> 00:21:37,740
Mr. 5! Let's show them how
truly terrifying we can be!

321
00:21:37,910 --> 00:21:39,980
Let's do it, Miss Valentine!

322
00:21:39,980 --> 00:21:41,720
Yes, Mr. 5!

323
00:21:41,720 --> 00:21:47,460
Don't mock us! We're Baroque
Works Officer Agents!

324
00:21:47,460 --> 00:21:50,150
– Quit being so damn annoying!
– Quit being so damn annoying!

325
00:21:51,230 --> 00:21:53,160
– You're interfering...
– You're interfering...

326
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:56,890
– ...with our fight!
– ...with our fight!

327
00:22:20,190 --> 00:22:21,960
Damn, they're annoying!

328
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:23,950
What's their problem?!

329
00:22:28,170 --> 00:22:31,500
This can't be! What strength!

330
00:22:31,500 --> 00:22:33,800
Unbelievable!

331
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:37,070
Alright, then. Let's settle this!

332
00:22:37,070 --> 00:22:38,300
Yeah!

333
00:22:50,270 --> 00:22:52,360
Knock that off!

334
00:22:58,610 --> 00:23:01,850
What the heck are you guys doing?!

335
00:23:01,850 --> 00:23:04,520
It's just a good thing you
managed to keep the girl safe!

336
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:08,760
You almost let a billion
belly get away from us!

337
00:23:08,760 --> 00:23:10,100
Understand?!

338
00:23:11,080 --> 00:23:14,700
What are you talking about?

339
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:17,630
Why did you save me?

340
00:23:17,630 --> 00:23:20,800
Right! We need to talk about that!

341
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:23,840
It's like this... Won't you
make a contract with me?

342
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:25,810
Contract?

343
00:23:25,810 --> 00:23:27,800
Quit fighting!

344
00:23:35,220 --> 00:23:38,350
Oh! You should have
just said so, Zoro!

345
00:23:38,350 --> 00:23:43,210
I just figured you cut them all down 'cause
they didn't make any food you liked!

346
00:23:43,210 --> 00:23:45,360
Don't compare me to you!

347
00:23:46,660 --> 00:23:48,070
C'mon! Don't sweat it!

348
00:23:48,070 --> 00:23:50,180
I can't!

349
00:23:50,180 --> 00:23:52,550
I do appreciate your
saving me. Thank you.

350
00:23:52,550 --> 00:23:54,560
Why can't you?! You're a princess!

351
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:57,490
One billion shouldn't be much...

352
00:23:57,490 --> 00:24:00,190
Do you know of the kingdom
known as Alabasta?

353
00:24:00,190 --> 00:24:01,340
No.

354
00:24:01,340 --> 00:24:05,450
It's a peaceful kingdom known as
a great civilization and nation.

355
00:24:05,450 --> 00:24:07,350
Well, it used to be.

356
00:24:07,350 --> 00:24:09,950
Used to be? What about now?

357
00:24:09,950 --> 00:24:12,350
It's in the middle of a civil war.

358
00:24:12,350 --> 00:24:16,390
For years now, signs of
a revolution have begun to appear.

359
00:24:16,390 --> 00:24:20,520
The people revolted, and the
kingdom fell into total chaos...

360
00:24:22,500 --> 00:24:26,240
Then, one day, I heard
the name of an organization...

361
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:27,380
Baroque Works!

362
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:34,010
I learned that the populace was
being manipulated by this group.

363
00:24:34,010 --> 00:24:37,080
But there was a tight lid on
any other information than that,

364
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:38,750
and there was nothing I could do.

365
00:24:38,750 --> 00:24:40,300
That's when I asked Igaram,

366
00:24:40,300 --> 00:24:43,890
who always meddled in my
business since childhood, for help.

367
00:24:43,890 --> 00:24:45,290
The old tube hair guy?

368
00:24:45,290 --> 00:24:47,620
Tube? Oh, yes.

369
00:24:48,720 --> 00:24:52,030
I asked him if there was a way
I could infiltrate Baroque Works.

370
00:24:52,030 --> 00:24:55,030
Because that would let us see
who was pulling the strings,

371
00:24:55,030 --> 00:24:57,370
and what their goal was.

372
00:24:57,370 --> 00:25:00,040
You're a pretty high-spirited princess.

373
00:25:00,040 --> 00:25:03,300
So? Did you figure out
this goal of theirs?

374
00:25:04,570 --> 00:25:08,080
"The founding of an ideal nation."

375
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:10,710
That's what Igaram said, anyway.

376
00:25:10,710 --> 00:25:12,710
Oh, does that mean...

377
00:25:12,710 --> 00:25:14,450
Yes.

378
00:25:14,450 --> 00:25:17,150
The boss says it's
to create an ideal nation,

379
00:25:17,700 --> 00:25:19,620
but it's an enormous lie!

380
00:25:19,620 --> 00:25:24,290
The true goal is to
take over Alabasta Kingdom!

381
00:25:24,290 --> 00:25:28,330
I have to hurry back, tell everyone
the truth, and stop the fighting!

382
00:25:30,830 --> 00:25:32,870
I see.

383
00:25:32,870 --> 00:25:37,140
So that's the deal.
Now everything finally connects.

384
00:25:37,140 --> 00:25:41,080
There'd be no money
during a civil war, huh...

385
00:25:42,810 --> 00:25:44,150
Hey.

386
00:25:44,150 --> 00:25:46,580
Who is pulling the strings?

387
00:25:46,580 --> 00:25:48,650
Th-The boss' identity?!

388
00:25:48,650 --> 00:25:50,490
You shouldn't ask that!

389
00:25:50,490 --> 00:25:51,690
You know who it is, right?

390
00:25:51,690 --> 00:25:53,590
Don't ask me! Anything but that!

391
00:25:53,590 --> 00:25:56,860
Your lives will be put in danger, too!

392
00:25:56,860 --> 00:25:58,190
I think I'll pass on that!

393
00:25:58,190 --> 00:26:01,000
After all, these are guys trying
to take over an entire country!

394
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:03,400
They're obviously insanely
dangerous people!

395
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:04,830
Yes! They are!

396
00:26:04,830 --> 00:26:07,250
As strong as you people may be,
you'd never stand a chance

397
00:26:07,250 --> 00:26:09,390
against one of the
Seven Warlords of the Sea,

398
00:26:09,390 --> 00:26:10,820
Crocodile!

399
00:26:13,910 --> 00:26:14,900
Who, now?

400
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:18,910
You just said it.

401
00:26:26,470 --> 00:26:28,860
What was that bird and sea otter?!

402
00:26:27,070 --> 00:26:28,860
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

403
00:26:28,860 --> 00:26:29,970
Are they going to tell someone?!

404
00:26:28,860 --> 00:26:29,970
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

405
00:26:29,970 --> 00:26:32,630
Hey! A Warlord!

406
00:26:32,630 --> 00:26:33,640
Not too shabby!

407
00:26:33,640 --> 00:26:36,270
I-I'm very sorry! It just slipped out!

408
00:26:36,270 --> 00:26:37,670
Like that really fixes things now!

409
00:26:37,670 --> 00:26:40,660
Why did you have to drag
us down with you?!

410
00:26:42,670 --> 00:26:46,490
Being hunted by a Warlord
the moment we enter the Grand Line

411
00:26:46,490 --> 00:26:47,980
is too much to handle!

412
00:26:47,980 --> 00:26:49,760
We're lucky we can see him so soon!

413
00:26:49,760 --> 00:26:51,010
I wonder what he's like!

414
00:26:51,010 --> 00:26:52,820
Shut up, you two!

415
00:26:52,820 --> 00:26:54,920
It's been a short acquaintance,
but I thank you for everything!

416
00:26:54,920 --> 00:26:56,020
Where are you going?

417
00:26:56,020 --> 00:26:58,280
They don't know what we look
like yet! I'm running away!

418
00:27:02,860 --> 00:27:04,690
Wow! That's so good!

419
00:27:05,700 --> 00:27:08,160
I guess this means there's
nowhere to run now, huh?!

420
00:27:08,160 --> 00:27:09,370
I'm sorry!

421
00:27:09,370 --> 00:27:10,730
She's funny!

422
00:27:10,730 --> 00:27:13,350
Where was she planning
to run to, anyway?

423
00:27:13,350 --> 00:27:20,030
Guess that means all three of us are
on Baroque Work's hit list now.

424
00:27:20,030 --> 00:27:21,690
That's exciting for some reason!

425
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:26,820
I-I do have 500,000 belly in savings...

426
00:27:27,070 --> 00:27:30,170
Fear not!

427
00:27:30,170 --> 00:27:30,830
It's–

428
00:27:31,600 --> 00:27:33,800
♪ Ma, ma, ma... ♪

429
00:27:33,810 --> 00:27:36,010
It's all right! I have a plan!

430
00:27:36,010 --> 00:27:39,150
Igaram! What are those clothes?!

431
00:27:39,150 --> 00:27:41,920
You look hilarious in those, old guy!

432
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:44,020
It's idiot after idiot...

433
00:27:44,020 --> 00:27:47,320
Your Highness,
please listen to me carefully.

434
00:27:47,320 --> 00:27:49,590
Once Baroque Works' intelligence
network learns of something,

435
00:27:49,590 --> 00:27:51,880
pursuers may come after
you almost immediately.

436
00:27:51,880 --> 00:27:56,030
Therefore, I will pretend
to be you, like so,

437
00:27:56,030 --> 00:28:01,660
and sail straight to Alabasta
with three dummies on board.

438
00:28:01,870 --> 00:28:04,440
While the pursuers are busy with me,

439
00:28:04,440 --> 00:28:07,790
all of you will head to
Alabasta via the normal route.

440
00:28:07,790 --> 00:28:10,420
Take the princess there? What now?

441
00:28:11,060 --> 00:28:13,970
Pops here wants us to take her home.

442
00:28:13,970 --> 00:28:16,210
Oh, that's what this is about?

443
00:28:16,210 --> 00:28:16,950
Sure!

444
00:28:17,230 --> 00:28:20,100
Crocodile is gonna come
after us, you know!

445
00:28:20,100 --> 00:28:22,840
Is Crocodile really that strong?

446
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:25,310
He's one of the
Seven Warlords of the Seas.

447
00:28:25,310 --> 00:28:29,510
He's a legally-recognized pirate,
and thus has no bounty on his head.

448
00:28:29,510 --> 00:28:34,950
However, the bounty he did have
long ago was 80 million belly.

449
00:28:34,950 --> 00:28:39,240
Eighty million?! That's four
times Arlong's bounty! Say no!

450
00:28:39,240 --> 00:28:41,340
♪ Ma, ma, ma... ♪

451
00:28:41,340 --> 00:28:44,270
Now, then. I, Vivi, will leave from here.

452
00:28:44,270 --> 00:28:45,940
That's a perfect imitation, old guy!

453
00:28:45,940 --> 00:28:47,670
Imitation of who?!

454
00:28:48,880 --> 00:28:52,680
Now then, Princess.
Please give me the eternal pose.

455
00:28:55,480 --> 00:28:57,520
Eternal pose?

456
00:28:57,520 --> 00:28:58,950
You've never heard of it?

457
00:28:58,950 --> 00:29:02,290
I suppose you could say it's
a permanent version of a log pose.

458
00:29:02,290 --> 00:29:06,230
Whereas a log pose always
leads ships to the next island,

459
00:29:06,230 --> 00:29:11,130
an eternal pose will never forget the magnetic
energy of the island that is stored in it.

460
00:29:11,130 --> 00:29:14,640
Meaning it will forever
point to that island alone.

461
00:29:14,640 --> 00:29:18,640
And this one is set to Alabasta.

462
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:21,630
You're going to use this to go to Alabasta?

463
00:29:23,080 --> 00:29:27,780
Princess Vivi, please take the indirect,
island-hopping route to Alabasta.

464
00:29:27,780 --> 00:29:29,950
I've not taken the path myself,

465
00:29:29,950 --> 00:29:32,720
but it should only be two or three
islands if you follow the log.

466
00:29:35,790 --> 00:29:38,860
Please take good care of the princess.

467
00:29:38,860 --> 00:29:39,430
Yeah!

468
00:29:39,430 --> 00:29:40,390
Igaram...

469
00:29:43,970 --> 00:29:46,970
I expect it will be a harsh journey.

470
00:29:46,970 --> 00:29:48,470
Be careful on your way.

471
00:29:48,470 --> 00:29:49,460
Iga...!

472
00:29:57,210 --> 00:29:58,540
You, too!

473
00:30:02,750 --> 00:30:05,320
Let us meet safely at our motherland.

474
00:30:09,790 --> 00:30:12,760
You must save the kingdom
by your own hand!

475
00:30:13,830 --> 00:30:15,530
There he goes.

476
00:30:15,530 --> 00:30:18,170
He was a funny old guy,
to the very end!

477
00:30:18,170 --> 00:30:21,140
He really is reliable.

478
00:30:47,300 --> 00:30:48,790
No!

479
00:30:54,170 --> 00:30:57,730
That's impossible!
They're already after us?!

480
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:08,350
He was a great person!

481
00:31:08,350 --> 00:31:10,090
Nami! What's the log say?!

482
00:31:10,090 --> 00:31:11,690
We're okay! It's stored up!

483
00:31:12,220 --> 00:31:14,020
Bring her with us! We're setting sail!

484
00:31:14,320 --> 00:31:15,490
Vivi! Vivi!

485
00:31:15,490 --> 00:31:19,190
Hurry! If they find us,
it'll all be for nothing!

486
00:31:22,700 --> 00:31:25,930
Don't worry! We will get you there!

487
00:31:25,930 --> 00:31:28,870
I know they don't look like it...

488
00:31:27,540 --> 00:31:29,710
Luffy! Go wake those two up!

489
00:31:28,870 --> 00:31:30,870
but they saved the East Blue!

490
00:31:30,110 --> 00:31:31,170
I'm going to the ship!

491
00:31:30,870 --> 00:31:32,140
Just the four of them!

492
00:31:31,170 --> 00:31:32,140
Alright! Leave it to me!

493
00:31:32,770 --> 00:31:36,910
Baroque Works?! Crocodile?! Ha!

494
00:31:38,220 --> 00:31:40,670
The Seven Warlords are nothing at all!

495
00:31:49,300 --> 00:31:50,960
Let's go!

496
00:31:53,500 --> 00:31:55,940
What the...?! Oww! What the...?!

497
00:31:55,940 --> 00:31:57,570
What the hell are you
doing, Luffy?! Hey!

498
00:31:57,570 --> 00:31:58,630
My nose is coming off!

499
00:31:58,630 --> 00:32:02,170
Let go, dammit! What's going on?!

500
00:32:02,980 --> 00:32:04,280
Hurry, Vivi!

501
00:32:04,280 --> 00:32:06,120
R-Right!

502
00:32:06,120 --> 00:32:07,480
Karoo is missing!

503
00:32:13,760 --> 00:32:14,900
A decoy.

504
00:32:15,780 --> 00:32:17,680
How foolish...

505
00:32:19,260 --> 00:32:20,960
Hey! I brought 'em!

506
00:32:20,960 --> 00:32:23,000
Get on! We're ready to leave anytime!

507
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:27,370
Huh? These guys are still sleeping!

508
00:32:27,370 --> 00:32:29,540
There's no time to look for him!

509
00:32:29,540 --> 00:32:31,570
But I can't just leave him here!

510
00:32:31,570 --> 00:32:32,240
Still!

511
00:32:32,240 --> 00:32:33,580
Hey! What's the problem?!

512
00:32:33,580 --> 00:32:36,080
She says her duck is missing!

513
00:32:36,080 --> 00:32:38,810
He won't come when
we whistle for him!

514
00:32:39,920 --> 00:32:41,350
This him?

515
00:32:41,350 --> 00:32:42,380
– You're there?!
– You're there?!

516
00:32:42,380 --> 00:32:44,190
He was here even before me.

517
00:32:44,190 --> 00:32:46,190
There's a tributary just up the river!

518
00:32:46,190 --> 00:32:48,190
We can use it to get
out to sea a little faster!

519
00:32:48,190 --> 00:32:50,590
Alright! Let's go!

520
00:32:51,960 --> 00:32:53,050
Hey.

521
00:32:54,300 --> 00:32:55,400
Mr. Bushido...

522
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:58,900
Just how many people are
gonna be chasing us down?

523
00:32:58,900 --> 00:33:00,470
I don't know.

524
00:33:00,470 --> 00:33:03,870
There are about 2,000
people in Baroque Works,

525
00:33:03,870 --> 00:33:08,340
and I've heard there are several
town-like bases like this one nearby.

526
00:33:08,340 --> 00:33:10,250
They really might send 1,000 people?!

527
00:33:10,250 --> 00:33:11,880
H-Huh?!

528
00:33:11,880 --> 00:33:13,720
Hey! The ship's leaving!

529
00:33:13,720 --> 00:33:15,280
Finally awake, I see.

530
00:33:15,280 --> 00:33:17,550
Wait! Let's stay just one more night!

531
00:33:17,550 --> 00:33:18,350
Yeah!

532
00:33:18,350 --> 00:33:20,560
This town is great!
And the girls are cute!

533
00:33:20,560 --> 00:33:22,890
There's no telling when
we'll have this much fun again!

534
00:33:22,890 --> 00:33:24,720
Let's take it easy! We are pirates!

535
00:33:24,720 --> 00:33:26,660
Plus, it's not even morning yet!

536
00:33:26,660 --> 00:33:29,890
They have some nerve.
They don't even know anything...

537
00:33:30,630 --> 00:33:32,570
Hey! Explain to them!

538
00:33:32,570 --> 00:33:33,860
Yep! I just did!

539
00:33:33,860 --> 00:33:35,640
That was fast...

540
00:33:35,640 --> 00:33:37,970
Yeah, I left out the complicated parts.

541
00:33:39,340 --> 00:33:41,280
We should be able to
leave the island soon...

542
00:33:41,280 --> 00:33:43,610
Cool! There's fog now!

543
00:33:43,610 --> 00:33:46,070
It's almost morning...

544
00:33:47,620 --> 00:33:49,650
It's good we managed to escape
the people chasing us!

545
00:33:49,650 --> 00:33:51,650
That's for sure!

546
00:33:51,650 --> 00:33:55,060
We need to be careful not to
crash the ship into the rocks.

547
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:57,550
This is a nice ship.

548
00:34:01,280 --> 00:34:02,150
Who're you?!

549
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:06,300
I ran into Mr. 8 a short while ago,

550
00:34:06,300 --> 00:34:08,120
Miss Wednesday.

551
00:34:08,830 --> 00:34:10,690
Did you kill Igaram?!

552
00:34:10,690 --> 00:34:12,440
Forget about that!

553
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:15,780
What're you doing
on this ship?! Who are you?!

554
00:34:15,780 --> 00:34:18,160
What are you doing here...

555
00:34:18,160 --> 00:34:20,130
Miss All-Sunday?!

556
00:34:18,160 --> 00:34:22,710
Miss All-Sunday
Vice President (Supreme Commander)
Baroque Works

557
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:27,290
Miss All-Sunday?!
What number is she partner to?!

558
00:34:27,290 --> 00:34:30,660
She's the partner of Mr. 0... the boss!

559
00:34:30,660 --> 00:34:32,960
The bo– Crocodile?!

560
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:34,230
Is she bad?

561
00:34:34,230 --> 00:34:37,830
She was the only one
who knew the boss' identity.

562
00:34:37,830 --> 00:34:41,890
We found out who
he is by following her!

563
00:34:41,890 --> 00:34:45,230
More accurately...
I allowed you to follow me.

564
00:34:45,230 --> 00:34:46,800
Oh! Then she's good!

565
00:34:46,800 --> 00:34:48,600
I know that!

566
00:34:48,600 --> 00:34:52,270
You're also the one who told him
we discovered his identity, right?!

567
00:34:52,270 --> 00:34:53,210
Correct.

568
00:34:53,210 --> 00:34:54,940
So she really is bad!

569
00:34:54,940 --> 00:34:56,840
Pipe down, you!

570
00:34:56,840 --> 00:35:00,550
What exactly is it you're trying to do?!

571
00:35:00,550 --> 00:35:02,980
Good question.

572
00:35:02,980 --> 00:35:07,890
You were all so intent and serious
that I found myself helping out.

573
00:35:07,890 --> 00:35:10,720
The idea of a princess trying
her hardest to save her kingdom

574
00:35:10,720 --> 00:35:13,560
while making herself
an enemy of Baroque Works...

575
00:35:13,560 --> 00:35:17,400
It was just so ridiculous, you see...

576
00:35:17,400 --> 00:35:19,990
Don't you mock me!

577
00:35:23,770 --> 00:35:27,940
Hey! Sanji! You do realize
what you're doing?!

578
00:35:27,940 --> 00:35:30,180
No... not really.

579
00:35:30,180 --> 00:35:34,010
I just sense that my beloved
Miss Wednesday is in danger...

580
00:35:34,010 --> 00:35:38,250
I'd appreciate it if you wouldn't
point such dangerous objects at me.

581
00:35:39,850 --> 00:35:40,840
You don't mean...!

582
00:35:41,390 --> 00:35:42,380
A devil–

583
00:35:43,860 --> 00:35:45,060
A devil fruit?!

584
00:35:45,060 --> 00:35:48,020
Which one?! What's her power?!

585
00:35:48,020 --> 00:35:50,160
Oww...

586
00:35:50,160 --> 00:35:53,030
Upon closer look, you're
actually a beautiful lady!

587
00:35:53,630 --> 00:35:55,890
Now, now. Don't be so hasty.

588
00:35:56,670 --> 00:35:59,980
I haven't been given any orders.

589
00:36:00,410 --> 00:36:02,670
I have no reason to fight.

590
00:36:04,380 --> 00:36:07,850
So you're the straw hat captain
I've heard so much about...

591
00:36:07,850 --> 00:36:10,310
Monkey D. Luffy.

592
00:36:10,310 --> 00:36:13,720
Hey, you! Gimme my hat back!
Are you trying to start a fight?!

593
00:36:13,720 --> 00:36:16,960
I deem you an enemy! Leave this instant!

594
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:18,560
How unlucky you are...

595
00:36:18,560 --> 00:36:23,500
You people who picked up a princess
Baroque Works is out to kill...

596
00:36:23,500 --> 00:36:27,370
And a princess being protected
by a mere handful of pirates...

597
00:36:27,370 --> 00:36:34,240
But what's even unluckier is the
course your log pose indicates.

598
00:36:34,240 --> 00:36:36,780
The name of the next island is...

599
00:36:36,780 --> 00:36:39,710
Little Garden.

600
00:36:39,710 --> 00:36:42,510
We don't even need to do anything,

601
00:36:42,510 --> 00:36:45,250
you'll be wiped out long before
you can even reach Alabasta.

602
00:36:45,250 --> 00:36:46,720
Will not! Gimme my hat back!

603
00:36:46,720 --> 00:36:48,750
You wish! You big dummy!

604
00:36:48,750 --> 00:36:51,060
What are you, a kid?

605
00:36:51,060 --> 00:36:55,460
Do you not think letting yourself
get wiped out is a bit foolish?

606
00:36:57,800 --> 00:36:59,430
An eternal pose?

607
00:36:59,870 --> 00:37:03,540
You can skip past
Little Garden with that.

608
00:37:03,540 --> 00:37:07,410
It points to an island
just before Alabasta:

609
00:37:07,410 --> 00:37:09,540
Nihiland.

610
00:37:09,540 --> 00:37:14,110
None of our employees know
that course, so no one will chase you.

611
00:37:15,750 --> 00:37:18,450
What? She's a good person?

612
00:37:18,450 --> 00:37:20,220
Why are you giving this to us?!

613
00:37:20,220 --> 00:37:21,720
It's a trap, isn't it?

614
00:37:23,120 --> 00:37:25,420
Is it, now?

615
00:37:25,420 --> 00:37:29,960
What do I do? I don't want to
accept this from someone like her.

616
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:32,730
But now that they've let me on board,

617
00:37:32,730 --> 00:37:34,730
taking the safest route might be best...

618
00:37:34,730 --> 00:37:37,700
Who cares about that!

619
00:37:42,410 --> 00:37:44,240
Are you an idiot?!

620
00:37:44,240 --> 00:37:47,710
She just went out of her way
to show us a nicer course!

621
00:37:47,710 --> 00:37:51,050
What if she's actually a good person?!

622
00:37:52,450 --> 00:37:55,580
You're not the one who
decides this ship's course!

623
00:37:59,930 --> 00:38:02,330
I see. That's too bad.

624
00:38:02,330 --> 00:38:03,060
Urgh!

625
00:38:03,060 --> 00:38:07,130
She blew up the old tube
hair guy, so I hate her!

626
00:38:07,130 --> 00:38:10,740
I don't hate high-spirited people.

627
00:38:10,740 --> 00:38:12,500
If you survive...

628
00:38:12,500 --> 00:38:14,210
let's meet again.

629
00:38:14,210 --> 00:38:15,200
No!

630
00:38:18,410 --> 00:38:20,210
Let's go, Bunchi!

631
00:38:23,580 --> 00:38:25,220
Wh-What is that?!

632
00:38:25,220 --> 00:38:26,890
Don't tell me it's a sea king!

633
00:38:26,890 --> 00:38:28,060
No...

634
00:38:28,060 --> 00:38:31,690
– Whoa! A turtle!
– Whoa! A turtle!

635
00:38:31,690 --> 00:38:34,160
What a huge turtle!

636
00:38:36,890 --> 00:38:41,360
I can't tell what that
woman is thinking one bit!

637
00:38:41,360 --> 00:38:43,470
Then there's no point
in thinking about it.

638
00:38:43,470 --> 00:38:46,230
We already got someone like
that on this ship, anyway.

639
00:38:46,230 --> 00:38:49,300
Hey! Explain what's going on!
None of this makes sense!

640
00:38:49,300 --> 00:38:51,510
Oh, Miss Wednesday! Don't tell me
you've joined the crew?!

641
00:38:51,510 --> 00:38:53,180
Hey! Explain already–

642
00:38:53,180 --> 00:38:55,270
Whoa! There's an ostrich on board!

643
00:38:56,040 --> 00:38:57,790
C'mon, what's going on?!

644
00:38:57,790 --> 00:38:59,020
Is it for food?

645
00:38:59,580 --> 00:39:03,120
Explain what's going on!

646
00:39:04,390 --> 00:39:06,990
I see.

647
00:39:06,990 --> 00:39:09,290
It's too bad I missed out on it,

648
00:39:09,290 --> 00:39:13,160
but there's still opportunity
for me to shine, too.

649
00:39:13,160 --> 00:39:14,330
Don't worry!

650
00:39:14,330 --> 00:39:18,400
Now that this sleeping prince has
awoken, your safety is guaranteed!

651
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:21,080
Whoa! Good thing I slept through it!

652
00:39:21,080 --> 00:39:23,180
Nami, are you jealous?

653
00:39:23,180 --> 00:39:24,610
Nope!

654
00:39:24,610 --> 00:39:29,610
Is it really all right
for me to be on this ship?

655
00:39:29,610 --> 00:39:31,810
I'll only trouble you all...

656
00:39:31,810 --> 00:39:34,950
What're you talking about?!
We know who you are now!

657
00:39:34,950 --> 00:39:38,490
If you didn't want to trouble us,
you should've done so from the start!

658
00:39:38,490 --> 00:39:39,650
I'm sorry.

659
00:39:39,650 --> 00:39:41,320
Right, Luffy?

660
00:39:41,320 --> 00:39:43,560
Yeah! I'm hungry!

661
00:39:43,560 --> 00:39:45,230
Maybe it doesn't matter at all?

662
00:39:45,230 --> 00:39:48,160
For now, looks like our
next destination is set.

663
00:39:48,160 --> 00:39:50,130
Little Garden, huh...?

664
00:39:50,130 --> 00:39:52,730
H-Hey, now! Will we be alright there?!

665
00:39:52,730 --> 00:39:56,400
Who knows! Let's go, men!

666
00:39:56,400 --> 00:39:57,530
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

667
00:40:00,180 --> 00:40:01,940
It'll be quite the sight...

668
00:40:01,940 --> 00:40:03,480
Little Garden...
